>>>>>>>>>>>>> Jenkins Pipeline file stages <<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<

1) specify the work agent
2) Environment
3) Now define the stages
4) Within the stages create the stage and then steps in the stage
5) also define the post build actions


For example:

1st stage >> Checkout
step - clone the git repository
step2 - define the branch
step3 - define the url of the repo and extension and clean the repo before checkout.

2nd stage >> Build
step - write a script to do build step

3rd stage >> Test
step - write a script to test.

4th stage >> Deploy
step - declare the ENV variable value

5th stage >> Post build action
step - if success
step2 - if failure
